		<td><b>Tools Used By Real NES Programmers</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Hi! I'm very new to NES and 6502 programming, and many of the tutorials I've read reference relatively modern tools like YY-CHR and ASM6. These tools are good, but I would like to know which assemblers and sprite editors, if any, were used to create real NES games like <em>Super Mario Bros.</em> and such in the 1980's. If they are available for download today, can you send me a link to download? Thanks in advance to anyone who replies.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


