	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />These two programs come to mind, and both are downloadable.  It looks like neither can be downloaded from these links, but if it's not available elsewhere and it's allowed, I could upload them here.  tUME is already on the nesdev front page, but it's only a link to an dead site (I'm not sure why I didn't upload the file at the time).<br /><a href="http://games.greggman.com/game/tume___the_universal_map_editor/" class="postlink">tUME</a><br /><a href="http://www.neswarpzone.com/colordreamsshrine1/nindraw.html" class="postlink">NinDraw</a><br /><br />It's not software, but I have a hardware device made in 1992 by Parallax called TurboROM.  It's an EPROM emulator.  I doubt it was used professionally for NES programming, but it's about old enough to have been possible.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


